nt with blue bird these would become the very last fordchassis school buses ever built several features of these prototypes were integrated into the vision introduced in  ec  blue bird vision conventional cowled chassis using the chassis of the vision the ec was a limitedproduction series of conventional prototypes intended for testing new production designs the ec used the hood later seen on the  vision along with a new roof and window design approximately  were produced in total company timelineedit blue bird corporation timeline –present buses by configuration s s s s s                                                 company ownership al luce family merrill lynch capital henlys plc peach county holdings cerberus capital publicly traded cerberus majority owner type a single rearwheel mbii by girardin micro bird srw micro bird mbii micro bird tseries dual rearwheel micro bird drw micro bird tseries drw mbiv by girardin micro bird g type b mini bird type c conventional sbcv cv vision vision vision type d all american forward engine  all american forward engine  all american afe all american tfetre all american rear engine various chassis aare blue bird all american rear engine  all american are all american dredfe tc forward engine tc forward engine tc forward engine tc rear engine tc rear engine tc nonschool buses city bird qbus xcel csseries ultra lfultra lmb ltc wanderlodge  body wanderlodge  body wanderlodge lxlxim manufacturing and assemblyedit traditionally school buses such as those produced by blue bird consist of components purchased from various outside suppliers and parts which are manufactured inhouse to the companys specifications these two categories of parts are then typically assembled into bodies which can be mounted onto chassis which have often been variations of those used in a myriad of truck applications productionwise the large home plant complex in fort valley georgia served as both a part manufacturing plant for the entire organization as well as one of the six locations where bodies were assembled from in house and purchased components parts and service were also located in fort valley as was wanderlodge wayside park a treeshaded motor home park for visiting wanderlodges adjacent to the wanderlodge plant blue bird corporation currently operates a single manufacturing facility in the united states the blue bird body company in fort valley georgia a second facility blue bird north georgia in lafayette georgia was closed august   in the past blue bird has had an international manufacturing presence with two factories in canada one in mexico and one in south america these have now all been closed due to changing market conditions and blue birds shift back to a lineup of school busbased vehicles blue bird corporation manufacturing facilities name location product lines year opened year closed notes united states blue bird body company fort valley georgia all american tc vision qbus cs parts see notes the first fort valley facility opened in  destroyed by fire in  present fort valley facility opened in  blue bird north georgia lafayette georgia vision conventional tc   closed august   blue bird midwest mount pleasant iowa tc conventional mini bird micro bird   blue bird east buena vista virginia conventional mini bird tc   blue bird wanderlodge fort valley georgia wanderlodge parts   originally opened as cardinal manufacturing canada blue bird canada brantford ontario canada tc conventional micro bird parts   blue bird also operated a facility in st lin quebec from  to  micro bird inc drummondville quebec canada micro bird mbii g  girardin minibus production facility worldwide facilities blue bird de mexico monterrey nuevo león mexico conventional   blue bird central america guatemala city guatemala see notes  s produced all american and conventional bodies on locally available chassis brandingedit blue bird company logo in steering wheel the blue bird company emblem painted on the roof of many of its buses since the early s is a silhouette profile of its namesake a bluebird although the origin of the company name is no longer known several theories are known to exist most commonly in the early s al luce was perceived to have been nervous about using the family surname for the company out of fears of it being mispronounced ie the loose bus when showing a blue and yellow demonstrator unit to school officials luce overheard the positive reception of school children who had seen the bus who had nicknamed it a pretty blue bird luce chose that name for his body manufacturing company though school buses are painted yellow today imagesedit s blue bird all american fe bus in transit service in bronx ny s blue birdgmc as a mobile firefighting command center in quebec right hand drive blue bird tc in use with first essex in essex uk defunct  blue bird wheelchairequipped bus with international  chassis in kentucky see alsoedit companies portal wikimedia commons has media related to blue bird buses school bus north american bus industries list of school bus manufacturers referencesedit  blue bird corporation retrieved    a b c d httpsfinanceyahoocomquoteblbdfinancialspblbd  traxis group  httpwwwbluebirdcom blue bird corporation  a b c d e f g h i j k blue bird school bus history blue bird body co blue bird corp wanderlodge buddy luce albert l luce cardinal mfg fort valley georgia  coachbuiltcom wwwcoachbuiltcom retrieved    a b c mckeegan noel march   first steelbodied school bus donated to henry ford museum gizmagcom retrieved  november    a b c d e f g h i history of blue bird corporation – fundinguniverse fundinguniversecom retrieved    blue bird corporationabout ushistory archived from the original on  retrieved    blue bird corporation to relocate micro bird production blue bird press release may    a b httpwwwsecinfocomdrqwmfhtmdp blue bird body co  k annual report  x reg sk item   a b httpwwwafdcenergygovpdfssucpdf  a b blue bird envirobus  school bus blue bird corporation